---

<PageShell
  title="New Zealand Investor Visa 2026: Active Investor Plus & Entrepreneur Guide"
  description="Complete guide to New Zealand's Active Investor Plus Visa (NZD 5-15M) and Entrepreneur Visa. Investment requirements, insurance recommendations, and path to residence."
  headline="New Zealand Investor Visa: Investment & Insurance Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about New Zealand's Active Investor Plus and Entrepreneur visas—NZD 5-15 million thresholds, business requirements, and healthcare planning for the land of opportunity."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official Immigration NZ Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      ACC Injury Coverage for All
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      New Zealand's investor visa program underwent a major overhaul in 2022, replacing the previous Investor 1 and Investor 2 categories with the streamlined Active Investor Plus visa. The new program emphasizes "active" investment—capital that contributes to New Zealand's economy through growth companies, venture capital, and listed equities rather than passive instruments like government bonds.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For entrepreneurs without multi-million-dollar capital, the Entrepreneur Work Visa offers a lower entry point at NZD 100,000, allowing you to establish and operate a high-value business before transitioning to residence. Both pathways lead to New Zealand's exceptional quality of life: clean air, outdoor adventures, excellent education, and a stable democracy.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: New Zealand Investor/Entrepreneur Visas</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Active Investor Plus:</strong> NZD 5M (direct), NZD 10M (listed equities), NZD 15M (with property)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Entrepreneur Work Visa:</strong> NZD 100,000 capital for high-value business</li>
        <li>• <strong>Investment period:</strong> 4 years for Active Investor Plus</li>
        <li>• <strong>Entrepreneur pathway:</strong> 3 years work visa, then residence after 2 years success</li>
        <li>• <strong>Health insurance:</strong> Not mandatory, but strongly recommended</li>
        <li>• <strong>ACC coverage:</strong> Automatic injury coverage for everyone in NZ</li>
        <li>• <strong>English requirement:</strong> Applies to Active Investor Plus applicants</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to residence:</strong> After 4-year investment period (Active Investor Plus)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Application fee:</strong> NZD 4,310 (Active Investor Plus)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Choose New Zealand?</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• World-class quality of life and natural beauty</li>
          <li>• Stable economy and political system</li>
          <li>• English-speaking, business-friendly environment</li>
          <li>• No capital gains tax on most investments</li>
          <li>• Excellent education system for families</li>
          <li>• Clean, green lifestyle appeal</li>
          <li>• ACC covers all accident-related injuries</li>
          <li>• Path to citizenship after 5 years residence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• High investment threshold (NZD 5-15 million)</li>
          <li>• "Active" investment requirement—not passive bonds</li>
          <li>• Geographic isolation from major markets</li>
          <li>• No public healthcare until residence</li>
          <li>• Smaller economy limits some opportunities</li>
          <li>• High cost of living, especially Auckland</li>
          <li>• 4-year investment maintenance period</li>
          <li>• English proficiency requirement</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>2022 program changes:</strong> The Active Investor Plus visa replaced the old Investor 1 (NZD 10M) and Investor 2 (NZD 3M) categories. The new program focuses on "growth investments" that benefit New Zealand's economy. Government bonds and bank deposits no longer qualify. Applicants must demonstrate willingness to share business experience with NZ enterprises.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">New Zealand Investor Visa is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>You have NZD 5+ million to invest actively</li>
          <li>You value quality of life over proximity to markets</li>
          <li>You want an English-speaking environment</li>
          <li>You appreciate outdoor lifestyle and nature</li>
          <li>You have business experience to contribute</li>
          <li>You can commit to a 4-year investment period</li>
          <li>You're comfortable with private health insurance</li>
          <li>You want a stable, corruption-free society</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You have less than NZD 5 million to invest</li>
          <li>• You prefer passive investments (bonds, deposits)</li>
          <li>• You need proximity to Asian or European markets</li>
          <li>• You want faster path to residence</li>
          <li>• You require immediate public healthcare access</li>
          <li>• You don't meet English proficiency requirements</li>
          <li>• You want a lower cost of living</li>
          <li>• You prefer larger urban centers</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Active Investor Plus vs. Entrepreneur Pathway</h3>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Criteria</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Active Investor Plus</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Entrepreneur Visa</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Minimum Capital</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">NZD 5-15 million</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">NZD 100,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Time to Residence</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">4 years</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">5+ years (3+2)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Business Involvement</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Share experience; active investing</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Full-time business operation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Points System</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">No points required</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Points-based assessment</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">English Requirement</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">IELTS 5.0 or equivalent</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">IELTS 4.0 or equivalent</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Who should choose which:</strong> Active Investor Plus suits high-net-worth individuals who want to invest passively in growth assets while contributing occasional business expertise. The Entrepreneur pathway suits those who want hands-on involvement in building a business in New Zealand with lower capital requirements.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Visa Requirements -->
  <section id="visa-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      New Zealand offers two main pathways for investor and entrepreneur immigration. The Active Investor Plus visa is for high-net-worth individuals, while the Entrepreneur visa provides a lower-capital alternative for those willing to build a business.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-6 mb-3">Active Investor Plus Visa Requirements</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={investorColumns} rows={investorRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">What Qualifies as "Active Investment"?</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The 2022 overhaul specifically excludes passive investments. Qualifying investments must contribute to New Zealand's productive economy:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Qualifying Investments</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Growth-stage NZ private companies</li>
          <li>• Venture capital and private equity funds</li>
          <li>• Managed funds investing in NZ growth</li>
          <li>• NZX-listed equities (NZD 10M+ pathway)</li>
          <li>• Commercial property (limited weighting)</li>
          <li>• Philanthropic investments in NZ</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-red-200 bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Non-Qualifying Investments</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
          <li>• Government bonds</li>
          <li>• Bank deposits</li>
          <li>• Personal assets (cars, boats, art)</li>
          <li>• Owner-occupied residential property</li>
          <li>• Investments outside New Zealand</li>
          <li>• Passive income-generating assets</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Entrepreneur Work Visa Requirements</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Entrepreneur Work Visa is for those who want to establish and actively manage a business in New Zealand. Requirements include:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Minimum capital:</strong> NZD 100,000 for high-value businesses (may be waived for exceptional innovation)</li>
      <li><strong>Business plan:</strong> Detailed plan demonstrating benefit to New Zealand</li>
      <li><strong>Business experience:</strong> Relevant background in the proposed business area</li>
      <li><strong>Points threshold:</strong> Must score 120 points on the Entrepreneur scale</li>
      <li><strong>English proficiency:</strong> IELTS 4.0 overall or equivalent</li>
      <li><strong>Character and health:</strong> Standard immigration requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Not purchasing existing business:</strong> Generally must create new enterprise</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Entrepreneur Pathway to Residence</h4>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">After successfully operating your business for 2+ years under the Entrepreneur Work Visa, you can apply for the Entrepreneur Resident Visa. You must demonstrate your business has been beneficial to New Zealand (employment creation, export growth, innovation, etc.).</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">English Language Requirements</h3>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Active Investor Plus</h4>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">IELTS 5.0 or equivalent, or evidence of English-language business dealings or education. The requirement can also be met through:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-neutral-600">
        <li>University degree taught in English</li>
        <li>Background in English-speaking business environment</li>
        <li>Native English speaker from approved country</li>
        <li>IELTS, TOEFL, PTE, or Cambridge English tests</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Unlike some investor visas, New Zealand's Active Investor Plus has no minimum stay requirement during the investment period. However, you must invest your funds in qualifying NZ investments within 12 months of visa approval and maintain them for 4 years.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Health Insurance: Not Mandatory, But Essential</h3>
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        Unlike some countries, New Zealand does not require health insurance for investor visa holders. However, without residence status, you have no access to New Zealand's public healthcare system (except for emergencies and ACC-covered injuries). Comprehensive private insurance is strongly recommended.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      New Zealand has a unique healthcare situation for temporary visa holders. While you won't have access to subsidized public healthcare, you will be automatically covered by ACC (Accident Compensation Corporation) for any injury—regardless of visa status. This covers treatment for injuries from accidents, but not illness.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Understanding ACC (Accident Compensation Corporation)</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">What ACC Covers</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>Treatment for accidental injuries</li>
          <li>Sports injuries and adventure activities</li>
          <li>Work-related accidents</li>
          <li>Motor vehicle accident injuries</li>
          <li>Rehabilitation services</li>
          <li>Weekly compensation if unable to work</li>
          <li>Medical treatment costs for injuries</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">What ACC Does NOT Cover</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>Illness and disease</li>
          <li>Chronic health conditions</li>
          <li>Preventive care and check-ups</li>
          <li>Mental health (unless injury-related)</li>
          <li>Maternity care</li>
          <li>Prescription medications (non-injury)</li>
          <li>Dental care (non-injury)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Private Insurance is Essential</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      As an investor visa holder, you'll pay full cost for any non-ACC healthcare. A single hospital admission can cost NZD 20,000-100,000+. Consider these scenarios:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Heart condition:</strong> Not covered by ACC—full private cost or health insurance</li>
      <li><strong>Cancer treatment:</strong> Chemotherapy can cost NZD 50,000+ without coverage</li>
      <li><strong>Appendectomy:</strong> Emergency surgery approximately NZD 15,000-25,000</li>
      <li><strong>Chronic condition management:</strong> Ongoing costs add up quickly</li>
      <li><strong>Maternity care:</strong> Full pregnancy and birth package NZD 10,000-20,000</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-green-800">
        <strong>Our recommendation:</strong> Budget NZD 3,000-8,000 annually for comprehensive private health insurance. For high-net-worth investors, international plans from Cigna Global or Bupa Global provide worldwide coverage with premium service. New Zealand-based insurers like Southern Cross offer excellent local coverage at lower cost.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Box -->
  <CTABox
    variant="highlight"
    title="Need insurance for your New Zealand investor visa?"
    description="Compare international and NZ-based insurers that provide comprehensive coverage for visa holders."
    buttonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <!-- Section: Recommended Providers -->
  <section id="recommended-providers" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Investor visa holders typically choose between international insurers offering worldwide coverage and New Zealand-based private insurers with strong local networks. Your choice depends on travel frequency, budget, and coverage preferences.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Provider Recommendations by Situation</h3>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">High-Net-Worth / Frequent Traveler</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">If you maintain homes in multiple countries or travel extensively, choose Cigna Global or Bupa Global. These provide seamless worldwide coverage—you can receive treatment in Auckland, Sydney, Singapore, or London without changing plans. Premium service includes direct billing at top hospitals globally.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Primarily NZ-Based / Budget-Conscious</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">If you'll spend most time in New Zealand, Southern Cross or nib offer excellent coverage at roughly half the cost of international plans. Southern Cross is New Zealand's largest private health insurer with well-established hospital relationships. These plans are NZ-focused but may include some overseas coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Family Coverage</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Bupa Global offers particularly strong family plans with comprehensive pediatric coverage. For a family of four, budget NZD 1,200-2,500/month for international coverage, or NZD 500-1,200/month for New Zealand private insurance. Consider education integration—some plans include overseas student coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Pre-existing Conditions</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">International insurers like Cigna Global typically offer better coverage for pre-existing conditions after waiting periods (usually 12-24 months). New Zealand insurers may exclude conditions permanently or require longer waiting periods. Disclose all conditions upfront—non-disclosure can void your policy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Tip for investors:</strong> Remember that ACC covers all accident-related treatment regardless of insurance. Your private policy primarily covers illness and non-injury conditions. Some investors opt for less comprehensive (and cheaper) illness-only coverage knowing ACC handles accidents.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

