    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Here's how different situations typically play out for investor visa applicants:
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">US Tech Entrepreneur, NZD 8M Investment</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">50 years old, sold tech company, seeking lifestyle change. Invested in NZ venture capital funds and growth-stage tech companies.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">Approved after 4 months. Chose Cigna Global for worldwide coverage (NZD 650/month). Now splits time between Auckland and California. Actively mentoring NZ startups as part of visa commitment. Plans to transition to residence after investment period, appreciating work-life balance and outdoor lifestyle.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Asian Family, NZD 15M Property Pathway</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Family of four seeking education opportunities for children. Used highest-threshold pathway including residential property in Auckland.</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 font-medium">Approved for entire family. Purchased NZD 6M Auckland home plus NZD 9M in listed equities and managed funds. Bupa Global family plan (NZD 1,800/month). Children enrolled in top Auckland schools. Appreciating NZ education system and outdoor lifestyle. Planning permanent relocation after residence obtained.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">UK Entrepreneur, NZD 100K Business Visa</h3>
